translated: Larsson, Lars Albin, senior teacher, principal, Ulricehamn, b. 5/3/85 in Övre Ulle-rud, Värmland, son of lay judge Lars Magnus Eriksson and Karohna Andersson. Married 1. 10/xx to Ester Nilsson, d. 1936; 2. 1942 to subject teacher Stina Johansson. Children: Brita b.1913, Lars-Magnus b.1944. — Graduated from elementary school teacher program in Karlstad in 1906. Substitute elementary school teacher in Karlskoga in 1906, regular position in Färnebo 1907-1915, in Ulricehamn since 1916, senior teacher there since 1929, also principal of vocational school since 1930. City council member from 1919-1926 and 1942-1946, board member of Västergötland sports association 1920-1926, school board member since 1922, board member of Skara Diocese Teachers' Association 1928-1938, chairman of the Älvsborg district of the Swedish elementary school teachers' association 1929-1935, vice chairman of the child welfare board since 1930, administrator and auditor of Ulricehamns City and Redväg Savings Bank. Member of Odd Fellows Study Trip to Germany in 1921.
